gomodel:SYNGO_682  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: * Immunogold electron microscopy (EM) of rat CA1 hippocampus in vivo shows Triad3A immunogold labeling near the membrane and on vesicle-like structures in BOTH presynaptic terminals and postsynaptic spines (Figure 6E).\n\n23/10/2017 Pim\n- Authors mention: \"Triad3A labeling was present at membrane sites and vesicular structures in both presynaptic terminals (T) and postsynaptic spines (S).\". Experimental description: Supp info: Brain tissue was removed from deeply anesthetized Sprague-Dawley rats" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
